        <Historic_Flag>Current</Historic_Flag>
        <Parent_String>Mesopotamian (culture or style) [300019828], Near Eastern (Early Western World) [300019571], Early Western World [300019255], styles, periods, and cultures by region [300111079], Styles and Periods (hierarchy name) [300015646], Styles and Periods Facet [300264088]</Parent_String>
        <Hier_Rel_Type>Genus/Species-BTG</Hier_Rel_Type>
      </Preferred_Parent>
    </Parent_Relationships>
    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Style and culture of the ancient area of northern Mesopotamia, particularly from about 1500 to 1300 BCE, when the Mitanni kingdom flourished. The art of the period is characterized by fine ivory carving, glass and glaze production, bronze and iron working, and cylinder seals combining Babylonian, Egyptian, and Aegean motifs.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000083463/Edwards et al., Cambridge Ancient History (1970)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Se refiere al período de aproximadamente 1500 al 1300 a.C. en Mesopotamia del norte durante el que floreció el reino de Mitanni. El arte del período se caracteriza por tallado en marfil, producción de barniz y vidrio, trabajo en bronce y hierro, y sellos de cilindro que combinan motivos babilónicos, egipcios y egeos.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Verwijst naar de periode van circa 1500 tot 1300 v. Chr. toen in het noorden van Mesopotamië het Mittanische koninkrijk bloeide. De kunst uit deze periode kenmerkt zich door het fijne ivoorsnijwerk, de vervaardiging van glas en glazuur, brons en ijzerwerk. In de rolzegels worden Babylonische, Egyptische en Egeïsche motieven gecombineerd.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>指於西元前1500年至西元前1300年間，米坦尼王國於美索不達米亞北方興盛發展的時代。此時代的藝術特色為精美的象牙雕刻、玻璃與釉料的製造、銅器與鐵器工藝的發展，以及融合巴比倫、埃及與愛琴海圖樣的圓筒圖章。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
      </Descriptive_Note>
    </Descriptive_Notes>
